### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5005
@apiVersion = v1

# API Key Authentication (SysAdmin)
@apiKey = sk-Xnai-SEoFvTEYIuBRjdIJWYPWykvJoFUj1OeAOfP8FZk5vGE

### ============================================
### Admin API - Secret Vault
### ============================================
# Authentication: Authorization: Bearer <api-key>
# Key must be unique across the collection.
# TenantId/AgentId null = scope across tenants/agents; UserId null = any user; ActivationName null = any activation of the agent.

### 1. Create Secret
# Key must be unique. Optional: tenantId, agentId, userId, activationName, additionalData (JSON object or string; stored as JSON).
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/secrets
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "key": "my-api-key-03",
  "value": "super-secret-value-123",
  "tenantId": null,
  "agentId": null,
  "userId": null,
  "activationName": null,
  "additionalData": {
    "env": "prod",
    "service": "payment"
  }
}

###

### 2. Create Secret (cross-tenant, no additionalData)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/secrets
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "key": "shared-secret-key",
  "value": "shared-secret-value",
  "tenantId": null,
  "agentId": null,
  "userId": null,
  "activationName": null
}

###

### 3. List Secrets (no filter)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/secrets
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 4. List Secrets (filter by tenantId, agentId, and/or activationName)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/secrets?tenantId=99xio&agentId=agent-01&activationName=my-activation
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 5. Fetch Secret by Key
# Returns only value and additionalData. Scope by query: key, tenantId, agentId, userId, activationName.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/secrets/fetch?key=my-api-key-01
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 6. Fetch Secret by Key with scope
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/secrets/fetch?key=my-api-key-02&tenantId=99xio&agentId=agent-01&userId=user-123&activationName=my-activation
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 7. Update Secret by Key and Scope
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/secrets
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "key": "my-api-key-01",
  "value": "my-api-key-01",
  "tenantId": "99xio",
  "agentId": "agent-01",
  "userId": "user-123",
  "activationName": "my-activation",
  "additionalData": { "env": "prod", "updated": true }
}

###

### 8. Delete Secret by Key and Scope
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/secrets?key=my-api-key-01&tenantId=99xio&agentId=agent-01&userId=user-123&activationName=my-activation
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###
